<module>
    <h>gille</h>
    <p><g>gille</g>
        <masc/>
        <en>a boy</en></p>

    <section>
        <h>adjectives</h>
        <section id="adj-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <section id="adj-sbj-size">
                <h>size</h>
                <p><g>gille <a href="?gd=beag">beag</a></g>
                    <en>a little boy</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Càit a bheil an gille beag an diugh?</gd>
                            <tr>Where is the little boy today?</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>A bheil an gille beag anns an sgoil? Chan eil.</gd>
                            <tr>Is the little boy in the school? No, he isn’t.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Có tha anns a’ chraoibh? Tha an gille beag.</gd>
                            <tr>Who is in the tree? The little boy is.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 40</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Nigh an gille beag a làmhan.</gd>
                            <tr>The little boy washed his hands.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <gd>An do sheas an gille beag aig an uinneig? Sheas.</gd>
                            <tr>Did the little boy stand at the window? Yes, he did.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 54</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl></p>
                <p><g>gille <a href="?gd=moor">mór</a></g>
                    <en>a big boy</en> – <xl>
                        <li>
                            <gd>Tha an gille mór.</gd>
                            <tr>The boy is big.</tr>
                            <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                        </li>
                    </xl></p>
            </section>
        </section>
        <section id="adj-obj">
            <h>object</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=ceaarr">ceàrr</a> air gille</g>
                <en>wrong with a boy</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Dé tha ceàrr air a’ ghille seo? Tha a cheann goirt.</gd>
                        <tr>What is wrong with this boy? His head is sore.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>verbs</h>
        <section id="verbs-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=cluich">cluich</a> gille</g>
                <en>a boy plays</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an gille a’ cluich? Tha,</gd>
                        <tr>Is the boy playing? Yes, he is.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=nigh">nigh</a> gille ...</g>
                <en>a boy washes ...</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nigh an gille beag a làmhan.</gd>
                        <tr>The little boy washed his hands.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </section>
        <section id="verbs-obj">
            <h>object</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=buail">buail</a> ... gille</g>
                <en>... strikes a boy</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An do bhuail e an gille le bata? Bhuail.</gd>
                        <tr>Did he strike the boy with a stick? Yes, he did.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 44</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>An do bhuail i an gille le cloich? Cha do bhuail.</gd>
                        <tr>Did she strike the boy with a stone? No, she didn’t.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 44</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha do bhuail i an gille.</gd>
                        <tr>She didn’t strike the boy.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 44</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>nouns</h>
        <section id="nouns-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p><g>gille aig <a href="?gd=dorus">dorus</a></g>
                <en>a boy at a door</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Cha robh an gille aig an dorus.</gd>
                        <tr>The boy was not at the door.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 15</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
            <p><g>gille ann an <a href="?gd=sgoil">sgoil</a></g>
                <en>a boy in a school</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an gille beag anns an sgoil? Chan eil.</gd>
                        <tr>Is the little boy in the school? No, he isn’t.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="nouns-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p><g><a href="?gd=laamh">làmh</a> gille ...</g>
                <en>a boy’s hand</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Nigh an gille beag a làmhan.</gd>
                        <tr>The little boy washed his hands.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 47</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl></p>
        </section>
    </section>

    

